The Secret Life of Trees

About the fifth commandment: Apparently, trees naturally try to grow as quick as possible, but if they are in close proximity to their parent-tree as in a non-manmade forest, the parent tree significantly slows their growth speed through light deprivation - which causes the...

... child tree go grow slower, but also SIGNIFICANTLY increases its lifespan - the ones that grow quickly also tend to die and wither quickly. Thus the fifth commandment, namely respecting your father and mother, which will bring you long life, also seems to work for trees
